  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Business Dev&apos;t Services 4 SME in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Open Capital advisors in partnership with Oxfam will evaluate more than 200 SMEs, provide business support to 30 selected SMEs, andlead select SMEs through a capital raise process, targeting a successful raise for the selected SMEs ready to raise capital and aligning its incentives to help companies successfully raise by deferring a portion of their fees to be paid only if companies do raisecapital
over the three years OCA will screen 200 plus SMEs in Uganda, identify 30 high- potential SMEs for the annual cohort, and provide proprietary, proven form of tailored support to deliver three clear outcomes;
(i) improve and professionalize operations,
(ii) define a strategy for rapid growth
 (iii) in many cases, raise the capital needed to achieve growthplans.
They will tailor their support based on the businesses# needs and growth stage, but for each business they will offer the following support:
1. Group investment readiness training # all businesses will be invited to attend a 3-day training
2. Identification of biggest challenges # for all businesses they will work with them to identify their biggest challenges to growth, scale and capital raising
3. OCA support on select challenges # based on the skills already in-house, and the businesses# most pressing needs, they will identify the areas where OCA will offer support
4. Investor identification # they will identify at least 2 potential investors who are an appropriate fit forthe business, based on their capital need and growth stage
5. Investor introduction # finally they will introduce the businesses tothe identified investors</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="90">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">OPEN CAPITAL ADVISORS</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We founded Open Capital Advisors (OCA) in 2010 to unlock growth and investment in East and Southern Africa.  The creation of OCA was driven by a core gap our founders observed between businesses and investors in the region.  We saw many small growing businesses (SGBs) with massive potential and opportunity for scale, but who struggled to find financing to support their growth.  At the same time, we encountered investors who had available capital, but were unable to find sufficient businesses they deemed #investment ready#.  The investors required a higher level of formalization and strategic planning than the businesses they currently encountered in the market.
To bridge this gap OCA provides high-quality, intensive support to help our clients adapt to rapidly changing and growingmarkets, including co-designing strategies, implementing best practices, and raising external funds to drive growth and impact. We take significant risk alongside our SGB clients, typically deferring a portion of fees onto a successful capital raise. This approach allows us to work with businesses that would otherwise be unable to afford support. We have developed innovative programs with impact investors, USAID, and others to defray risk and work with even earlier-stage companies.
We target SGB clients looking to raise between $500K - $5M USD. These SGBs are trying to solve the toughest problems in their local markets, including agriculture, renewable energy, financial inclusion, and more. We select SGBs where our work will help them transform markets, create new jobs, and innovate products and services.
Today, Open Capital Advisors has offices incorporated in Kenya and Uganda with our team of 42 full-time professionals spread across Nairobi and Kampala.
Our approach to integrating gender has evolved and expanded in focus over the maturation of the firm.  We view our gender agenda as having two prongs: internal and external.
Internally, we focus on hiring, training and retaining highly talented employees, especially women.  As laid out in greater detail in our organogram below, over half of our entire team is female, and 50% of our senior management team (including 1 of two founding partners) is female.
In 2015 we hired a dedicated head of Human Resources who has studiedgender equity in the workplace.  She has helped us formalize our practices on gender equity, including updating our HR procedures and introducing a gender policy.
Externally, we work with and support promising entrepreneurs, many of whom are female.  Historically, 30% of the founders we have worked with have been women and we continue to focus on increasing this ratio.  Further, we work with many pro-women businesses, that include empowering women # in their workforce or throughtheir products / services# as a core component of their business model.</narrative>
